                                {
                                  "type": "text",
                                  "id": "gW1Mf",
                                  "name": "userBubble1Txt",
                                  "fill": "#C8C8C8",
                                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                  "width": 380,
                                  "content": "Why do large language models sometimes generate false information that sounds completely convincing?",
                                  "lineHeight": 1.5,
                                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                  "fontSize": 13,
                                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                                }
                              ]
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "frame",
                          "id": "EnOo5",
                          "name": "AI Message 1",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "children": [
                            {
                              "type": "frame",
                              "id": "thHJn",
                              "name": "AI Bubble",
                              "fill": "#13120F",
                              "cornerRadius": [
                                8,
                                8,
                                8,
                                2
                              ],
                              "stroke": {
                                "thickness": 0.5,
                                "fill": "#1A1916"
                              },
                              "layout": "vertical",
                              "gap": 8,
                              "padding": [
                                10,
                                14
                              ],
                              "children": [
                                {
                                  "type": "text",
                                  "id": "81ySz",
                                  "name": "aiBubble1Txt",
                                  "fill": "#A8A8A8",
                                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                  "width": 420,
                                  "content": "LLMs hallucinate because they are fundamentally pattern-completion engines, not knowledge retrieval systems. During training, they learn statistical correlations between tokens -- but these correlations don't encode truth values.",
                                  "lineHeight": 1.5,
                                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                  "fontSize": 13,
                                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                                },
                                {
                                  "type": "text",
                                  "id": "gxaUf",
                                  "name": "aiBubble1P2",
                                  "fill": "#808080",
                                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                  "width": 420,
                                  "content": "The core mechanism: at each step, the model produces a probability distribution over possible next tokens. It selects based on likelihood, not factual accuracy. When it encounters a gap, it fills it with the most statistically plausible completion.",
                                  "lineHeight": 1.5,
                                  "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                  "fontSize": 13,
                                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                                }
                              ]
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "frame",
                          "id": "3iSbd",
                          "name": "User Message 2",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "justifyContent": "end",
                          "children": [
